# The panels scene: the auxiliary-window grammar. Two surfaces with
# distinct titles; the inspector's advisory size is honored on a
# desktop; its chrome close fires the veto class — close_window drives
# the REAL close path (performClose / WM_CLOSE / gtk close), the guest
# records the request and confirms with destroy_window, and the count
# drops. Desktop-only: phone hosts reject create_window by capability.
expect_windows 2
expect_title "panels"
expect_title window#1 "inspector"
expect_window_size window#1 480x320
close_window window#1
expect label#0 "close requested"
expect_windows 1
